---
import Link from '@/components/link.astro'
import PageHead from '@/components/page-head.astro'
import ProjectCard from '@/components/project-card.astro'
import PublicationCard from '@/components/publication-card.astro'
import Layout from '@/layouts/layout.astro'
import { getAllProjects, getAllPublications } from '@/lib/data-utils'

const projects = await getAllProjects()
const publications = await getAllPublications()
---

<Layout class="max-w-3xl">
  <PageHead slot="head" title="About" />
  <section>
    <div class="min-w-full">
      <div class="prose mb-8">
        <p class="mt-0">
          I&apos;m <strong> Wee Joe</strong>, an AI research engineer
          interested in mechanistic interpretability, reinforcement learning, and
          emerging paradigms in agentic intelligence, particularly world models,
          multi-agent coordination, and the challenge of keeping post-AGI systems
          human-aligned.
        </p>
        <p>
          I am currently pursuing a <strong>BSc in Computer Science</strong> at{
            ' '
          }
          <Link href="https://www.ucl.ac.uk" external underline
            >University College London</Link
          >. Earlier, I completed a Diploma in Computer Engineering at{' '}
          <Link href="https://www.sp.edu.sg" external underline
            >Singapore Polytechnic</Link
          > (Apr 2020 to May 2023), where I graduated as valedictorian. I have also
          taken part in the{' '}
          <Link href="https://ases.stanford.edu" external underline
            >Stanford ASES Entrepreneurship Bootcamp</Link
          >.
        </p>
        <p>
          I believe these research directions are among the most consequential of
          our time. Mechanistic interpretability can make AI systems auditable
          and trustworthy, a prerequisite for deploying them in medicine,
          education, and governance. World models and multi-agent coordination
          unlock AI that genuinely reasons and collaborates, compressing decades
          of scientific progress into years. And getting alignment right is what
          determines whether the transition to post-AGI systems expands human
          agency or erodes it. The stakes make it the most meaningful problem I
          can work on.
        </p>
        <p>
          Want to collaborate? Reach me on{' '}
          <Link
            href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/tanweejoe"
            external
            underline
            data-posthog-contact="LinkedIn">LinkedIn</Link
          >{' '}
          or via{' '}
          <Link
            href="mailto:tanweejoe@gmail.com"
            underline
            data-posthog-contact="email">email</Link
          >.
        </p>
      </div>

      {
        publications.length > 0 && (
          <div class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-medium">Research</h2>
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
              {publications.map((pub) => (
                <PublicationCard publication={pub} />
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        )
      }

      <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-medium">Projects</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
        {projects.map((project) => <ProjectCard project={project} />)}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<script>
  function setupContactLinks() {
    document
      .querySelectorAll<HTMLAnchorElement>('a[data-posthog-contact]')
      .forEach((link) => {
        link.removeEventListener('click', (link as any).__posthogContactClick)
        ;(link as any).__posthogContactClick = () => {
          window.posthog?.capture('contact_link_clicked', {
            channel: link.dataset.posthogContact,
            href: link.href,
          })
        }
        link.addEventListener('click', (link as any).__posthogContactClick)
      })
  }

  document.addEventListener('astro:page-load', setupContactLinks)
</script>
